Paper Code: ETIT-302
Paper: Decision Science


UNIT- I
Descriptive Statistics, Presentation of Data, Measures of Central Tendency and Variation.
Probability - Concepts, Theorems, Bayesâ€™ Rule, Linear Programming, Formulation, Graphical and Simplex Method.
[T1][R1]

UNIT- II
Decision Sciences and Role of quantitative techniques, Steps in decision making.
Decision making under uncertainty, including optimism criterion, pessimism criterion, Laplace criterion, optimism criterion, Hurwicz criterion and Regret criterion.
Decision making under risk, Multistage decision making, Multi criteria decision making.
Posterior probabilities and Bayesian Analysis.
[T1][T2]

UNIT- III
Game Theory:
  2 person zero-sum games, concept of dominance, Pure and Mixed Strategy.
  Arithmetic, Algebraic, Matrix Algebra method.
  Solution by Dominance, Subgame and Linear programming method.
  Queuing Theory, Basic structure, Terminology, Classification, Birth and Death Process.
  Queuing Models upto 2 service stations.
[T1][R1]

UNIT-IV
Transportation Problems, Initial Basic Feasible Solution, Test for Optimality.
Assignment problems.
Network Analysis - PERT and CPM.
Network Models, Concept, Drawing network, identifying critical path, Calculating EST, LST, EFT, LFT, Slack and probability of project completion (CPM and PERT), Crashing of Network.
[T1][R3]


